  "prompt": "How do I convert a .txt file to a .xml file?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to convert a .txt file to .xml:\n\n1. Manual Method:\n- Open a text editor\n- Add XML tags manually\n- Save with .xml extension\n\n2. Using Programming Languages:\nPython example:\n```python\n# Read text file\nwith open('input.txt', 'r') as txt_file:\n    content = txt_file.read()\n\n# Create XML\nxml_content = f\"<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\\n<root>\\n{content}\\n</root>\"\n\n# Write XML file\nwith open('output.xml', 'w') as xml_file:\n    xml_file.write(xml_content)\n```\n\n3. Online Converters:\n- CloudConvert\n- Zamzar\n- Online-Convert.com\n\n4. Excel/Spreadsheet Software:\n- Open text file\n- Use \"Save As\" and select XML format\n\n5. XML Editing Tools:\n- XMLSpy\n- Oxygen XML Editor\n- EditiX XML Editor\n\nChoose method based on your specific requirements and technical skill level.\n\nTip: Ensure proper XML structure and valid tags when converting.",
